Athene linking exception
=========================

The Athene IDE is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License,
version 2.1 (see the LICENSE file).

This exception modifies those terms for two specific parts of the project, so
that programs you design and build with Athene can be distributed under any
license — including proprietary — exactly as with the Lazarus LCL/RTL.

Scope
-----

This exception applies ONLY to:

  1. The `athutil` package (athutil/athutil.go in the Athene source tree, and
     the copy that Athene writes into each generated project); and

  2. Any source code that Athene generates, such as the `app.gen.go` file
     emitted into a generated project.

It does NOT change the license of the Athene IDE itself (the form designer,
code editor, code generator, and LSP client). Those remain under the LGPL v2.1
with no exception.

The exception
-------------

As a special exception, the copyright holders give you permission to link the
covered code (defined in "Scope" above) with independent modules to produce an
executable, regardless of the license terms of those independent modules, and
to copy and distribute the resulting executable under terms of your choice,
provided that you also meet, for each linked independent module, the terms and
conditions of the license of that module. An independent module is a module
which is not derived from or based on the covered code. If you modify the
covered code, you may extend this exception to your version of it, but you are
not obligated to do so. If you do not wish to do so, delete this exception
statement from your version.

What this means in practice
---------------------------

  - You may build a closed-source application with Athene and sell it or
    distribute it under whatever license you choose.
  - You are only obliged to honour the LGPL for the covered code *itself* — for
    example, if you modify athutil.go and ship it, share those modifications.
  - Your own handler code (handlers.go) and application logic are entirely
    yours; they are independent modules under this exception.
  - Third-party dependencies keep their own licenses: gotk4 is MPL-2.0, and
    GTK4 is LGPL and is linked dynamically via the system libraries.

This file is informational; the authoritative grant is the exception statement
reproduced in the header of each covered source file.
